<subSubSection id="A4B3EFB8E92CFF86FF1CFC94FC5BFA50" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EC16BC33E92CFF86FF1CFC94FD3BFB90" blockId="30.[120,1225,225,1522]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
COMMENTS: The short, thick aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName id="2BA9C7B0E92CFF86FD26FC95FC97FC8E" authorityName="Grimaldi" authorityYear="2016" box="[658,801,786,812]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="mexiflora">
<emphasis id="DEDD6021E92CFF86FD26FC95FC97FC8E" box="[658,801,786,812]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">D. mexiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="2BA9C7B0E92CFF86FBA5FC95FB23FC8E" authorityName="Grimaldi" authorityYear="2016" box="[1041,1173,786,812]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="billheedi">
<emphasis id="DEDD6021E92CFF86FBA5FC95FB23FC8E" box="[1041,1173,786,812]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">D. billheedi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2BA9C7B0E92CFF86FFCCFCBEFEBDFCF3" authorityName="Grimaldi" authorityYear="2016" box="[120,267,824,849]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sevensteri">
<emphasis id="DEDD6021E92CFF86FFCCFCBEFEBDFCF3" box="[120,267,824,849]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">D. sevensteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, n. spp., and the Brazilian species 
<taxonomicName id="2BA9C7B0E92CFF86FD1DFCBEFCA9FCF3" authorityName="Val and Marques" authorityYear="1996" box="[681,799,824,849]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="aguape">
<emphasis id="DEDD6021E92CFF86FD1DFCBEFCA9FCF3" box="[681,799,824,849]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">D. aguape</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it is less curved in lateral view and the distiphallus differs as shown in fig. 13. Also, the surstylus of 
<taxonomicName id="2BA9C7B0E92CFF86FC74FCD8FBE5FCD5" authorityName="Grimaldi" authorityYear="2016" box="[960,1107,861,887]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="mexiflora">
<emphasis id="DEDD6021E92CFF86FC74FCD8FBE5FCD5" box="[960,1107,861,887]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">D. mexiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 8–12 slender, pointed prensisetae and ventral setae that are sclerotized; versus 7–9 shorter, more blunt prensisetae in the other species and ventral setae that are not sclerotized. The following features differ with 
<taxonomicName id="2BA9C7B0E92CFF86FEDEFC4BFE6AFC45" box="[362,476,973,999]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bromeliae">
<emphasis id="DEDD6021E92CFF86FEDEFC4BFE6AFC45" box="[362,476,973,999]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">bromeliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: aedeagus distinctly shorter and shaft thicker in lateral view, aedeagal angle 129°–142° (vs. bent at nearly a right angle in 
<taxonomicName id="2BA9C7B0E92CFF86FCE3FC74FC71FBAE" box="[855,967,1010,1036]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bromeliae">
<emphasis id="DEDD6021E92CFF86FCE3FC74FC71FBAE" box="[855,967,1010,1036]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">bromeliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), ventral setae of the surstylus moderately to distinctly sclerotized.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC16BC33E92CFF86FF1CFBBBFF48FB65" blockId="30.[120,1225,225,1522]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Female genitalia confirm the species distinction of 
<taxonomicName id="2BA9C7B0E92CFF86FD48FBB8FC3CFBF5" authorityName="Grimaldi" authorityYear="2016" box="[764,906,1085,1111]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="mexiflora">
<emphasis id="DEDD6021E92CFF86FD48FBB8FC3CFBF5" box="[764,906,1085,1111]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">D. mexiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a reduced number of oviscapt pegs unique for the group. Females in the 
<taxonomicName id="2BA9C7B0E92CFF86FD62FBE4FCF0FBDE" box="[726,838,1122,1148]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bromeliae">
<emphasis id="DEDD6021E92CFF86FD62FBE4FCF0FBDE" box="[726,838,1122,1148]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">bromeliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group typically have 15 or more oviscapt pegs; 
<taxonomicName id="2BA9C7B0E92CFF86FE92FB0EFE25FB00" authorityName="Grimaldi" authorityYear="2016" box="[294,403,1160,1186]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="mexiflora">
<emphasis id="DEDD6021E92CFF86FE92FB0EFE25FB00" box="[294,403,1160,1186]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">mexiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only 8–9. This reduction is due to loss of pegs 1–3 and pegs 12 and higher.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC16BC33E92CFF86FF1CFB54FC5BFA50" blockId="30.[120,1225,225,1522]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
The 
<collectingCountry id="94BEFCA3E92CFF86FF68FB54FE81FB4E" box="[220,311,1234,1260]" name="Jamaica" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
specimen (DBG 16) is distinctively smaller than the Mexican specimens (ca. 0.68× the thorax length, 0.70× the wing length), and it differs from the Mexican specimens in orbital seta ratios (see description above). As a unique specimen the consistency of these differences cannot be evaluated, and since the proportions and shape of the aedeagus are identical to those of the Mexican specimens the conservative approach is to include these into one species until additional data may prove otherwise. Male genitalia of the 
<collectingCountry id="94BEFCA3E92CFF86FC7EFA0BFBFBFA05" box="[970,1101,1421,1447]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
specimen (DBG 83) is nearly identical to that of the Mexican specimens except that DBG 83 has the distiphallus more drop-shaped in full ventral view, and prensisetae shorter.
</paragraph>
